# Authoritative, platform-independent line-ending policy.
# Overrides every contributor's personal core.autocrlf, on Windows/Mac/Linux.

# Default: auto-detect text vs. binary; text is ALWAYS stored with LF line endings in repo and worktree.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binaries (auto-detected too, but stated for safety — never normalized):
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary

# Quasi-binary TEXT that must keep CRLF (e.g. raw HTTP traffic).
# List the concrete paths/extensions here. Examples:
#   *.http                       text eol=crlf
#   path/to/raw-http-capture     -text
